A protein modification that effectively converts an L-asparagine residue to L-aspartate 4-methyl ester.

definition.value: The deamidation and methylation of L-asparagine has not been reported as a natural modification. It is extremely unlikely that eukaryotes produce this modification, because a natural process that would form L-aspartic acid 4-methyl ester from either L-aspartic acid or L-asparagine would interfere with the D-aspartyl peptide repair mechanism [JSG].
